I. How to build primesieve (Windows, Linux, Mac OS X)
=====================================================

  Prerequisites
  -------------
  Since version 3.5 primesieve requires OpenMP 3.0 or later (2008).
  If your compiler only supports OpenMP <= 2.5 (e.g. MSVC 2010, Apple
  g++ 4.2) then you have to switch to primesieve 3.4:
  http://primesieve.googlecode.com/files/primesieve-3.4-src.zip

  1. Download and install the Qt SDK from:
     http://qt.nokia.com/downloads

  2. Launch the primesieve.pro project file with the Qt-Creator IDE
     and have a look at Qt-Creator-build-settings.png for the
     compilation steps.

II. Remarks
===========

  primesieve has been developed with Qt 4.7, if it does not compile
  with future releases of Qt old Qt4 builds can be retrieved from:
  ftp://ftp.trolltech.com/qt/source/

  The compiled primesieve executable depends on the QtGui4 and QtCore4
  libraries (Windows: .dll, Unix: .lib). You have to copy these
  libraries into the primesieve executable directory if you want to
  run it on other PCs.
